    "recap_headline": "Xavier University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "EUGENE, Ore.\n- Xavier dropped its series finale at Oregon, 6-3, on Wednesday night at PK Park.\nXavier moved to 5-13 on the year, while the Ducks improved to 14-3.\nThe Ducks took a 1-0 lead in the second inning on a\u00a0Naulivou Lauaki RBI single. Xavier responded in the top of the next inning with a two-out, RBI single from\nJosh Stonehouse\n.\nOregon broke open the scoreless game in the seventh inning, scoring five runs on four hits (all with two outs in the inning) to take a 6-1 lead.\nXavier responded with a\nJosh Stonehouse\ntwo-run homer in the eighth inning to close within three runs. The Musketeers recorded back-to-back hits from\nDonavan Canterberry\nand\nJorge Valdes\nfollowing the home run to keep the rally alive, but\nJason Jelic\nstruck out swinging to end the game.\nXavier had one more hit (9-8) than Oregon and left two more runners on base (7-5). The Musketeers committed the lone error of the game.\nXavier opens an eight-game homestand vs Evansville on Friday, March 13. First pitch is set for 3 p.m. from Hayden Field with the game being aired on ESPN+.\nAT THE PLATE\nJosh Stonehouse\nfinished 2-for-4 with three RBI, a run and homer. The freshman slugger now has a team-leading seven home runs\u00a0and 14 RBI.\nJD Crisp\nwent 2-for-4 with a double and a stolen base.\nJorge Valdes\nwent 2-for-2 with a double and a run.\nEddie Peters\nadded a double, while\nTanner Thomas\nand\nDonavan Canterberry\nboth added a single.\nThe Oregon pitching staff threw 16\u00a0strikeouts, the third most strikeouts in a game this season.\non the mound\nEvan Vasiliou\nmade his first start of the season, throwing a season-high 5.0 innings. The LHP threw a season-high three strikeouts. He allowed four hits and one run, while issuing one walk.\nOwen Poole\n(0-2) allowed two hits and four runs in 1.2 innings of relief. The RHP also walked one batter.\nGarrett Helsel\nrecorded one strikeout in 1.1 innings of relief. The LHP surrendered two hits and one run.\nHIGHLIGHTS"
